&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Practice Nurse&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Denbigh &amp; St Asaph &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Part-time &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking to recruit a Practice Nurse to join our team of Chronic Disease and Minor Illness Nurses, Assistant Practitioner, Heath Care Assistants, and Advanced Nurse Practitioner&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be dedicated to providing quality care and an empathetic, efficient service to our patients, including assessment, diagnosis and management of chronic disease.  Previous experience in childhood immunisations, travel vaccinations, cervical cytology, contraception and wound care would be beneficial, although full training and support will be provided. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Other duties may be offered dependent on previous experience and qualifications.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post will enable you to become an integral and valued part of a friendly, &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;supportive and efficient team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;No weekends or evenings working&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Stable and supportive environment&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Excellent administrative support&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Competitive salary&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NHS Pension Scheme&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;6 weeks annual leave, plus bank holidays&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Indemnity Cover&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Access to Confidential Employee Assistance Scheme&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Continued Personal and Professional Development&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing date: Sunday 22nd November&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
